(6, 1958071, 'Machining Specialist (Gears)', 'Internal Postings', 'Baguio City', 'Philippines', 'Open', '''<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">Our client, a leading industrial Fortune 500 Company has requested us to search for a couple of Machining Engineer positions for an overseas ex-pat assignment.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">You will be transferred to the Philippines to support the growth in their commercial line of business (Aircrafts). Relocation assistance is provided.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">The primary responsibility will be to perform manufacturing engineering assignments involving Mill-Turn lathes. This requires a working knowledge of turning concepts, lathe cutting tool selection, and troubleshooting. A working knowledge of milling concepts, part processing, cutting tool selection and troubleshooting, 3D solid modeling, and lean manufacturing knowledge is also necessary to be successful. Deburr, EDM, Honing, ID grinding, and Mazak machine knowledge is preferred.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<strong style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">Job Summary:</strong><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Identify, justify, and implement significant data driven projects to reduce manufacturing costs</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Apply lean manufacturing methods to cut product cycle time and costs while maintaining and improving part quality.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Troubleshoot existing manufacturing processes to identify & prioritize areas in need of improvement.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Troubleshoot a variety of manufacturing related problems, determine root cause solutions, and implement irreversible corrective action.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Troubleshoot cutting tool problems and determine root cause solutions.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Assist in smooth transitions of new processes and new production jobs into a production environment.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Apply fundamental engineering principles to create practical solutions to technical challenges.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Mentor, train, and lead less skilled manufacturing engineers on projects to improve metrics.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<strong style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">Educational & Experience Requirements:</strong><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• BS Degree (ME or IE preferred) and a minimum of 5 years manufacturing engineering experience.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<strong style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">OR</strong><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Additional seasoned experience in manufacturing engineering that would be equivalent to what is learned in a degreed program would be an acceptable alternative to the BS Degree requirement.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<strong style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">Other Qualifications:</strong><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Experience troubleshooting manufacturing issues in a production environment.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Demonstrated project leadership experience.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Strong computer skills, including Microsoft Word and Microsoft Excel</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Aerospace and/or hydraulic actuation experience preferred</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Must be able to work in a dynamic work environment with little supervision or daily direction.</span><br style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\" />\\n<span style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">• Strong, team-oriented professional with good interpersonal skills.</span>''', 'Active', 1, '2013-03-06', '2013-03-10 18:40:06');
INSERT INTO `job` (`id`, `joborder_id`, `title`, `company`, `city`, `state`, `salary`, `description`, `status`, `public`, `updated`, `date_reg`) VALUES
(7, 1975255, 'Quality Engineer', 'Internal Postings', 'Tultitlan', 'Edo. Mex.', '$20,000', '''<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">Our client, an International Tier 1 Automotive supplier has request us to search for two Quality Engineers for their facility in Tultitlan, Edo. de Mex.</div>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\"><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES</strong></div>\\n\\n<ul style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Under limited supervision, performs moderately complex tasks to develop, apply, and maintain quality requirements for processing components and other materials into finished goods and products.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Designs and implements methods and procedures for testing and inspecting the quality level of products and production equipment.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Reviews supporting manufacturing documentation ensure it contains the necessary criteria and provisions to permit effective inspection and testing of materials.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Recommends corrective action for procedural, product, or process deficiencies.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Analyzes instructions on routine assignments and detailed instruction on new assignments. </li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Reporting to the Manager of Quality, assist in improving the Quality Management System. This will be accomplished by the updating of departmental ISO 9001:2008/ TS 16949, and IS0 14001 documentation, audits, and corrective actions.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Preparing and writing technical documents such as test plans/reports, (i.e., failure analysis reports and Qualification/validation reports).</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Assist on first pass yield improvement, cost reductions, training, and utilizing scientific controls over the production process.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Perform other job related duties as assigned</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\"> </div>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\"><strong>EXPERIENCE</strong></div>\\n\\n<ul style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Years of Experience: 3 to 5 years experience in the Quality Assurance field, as well as with 5 S’s, LPA’s, QRQC.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Candidate must have competencies in word processing, spreadsheets, presentation software, statistical concepts, Minitab, root cause & corrective/preventive action, and MRB disposition.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Candidate must be a self-starter and work with limited supervision.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Candidate must be competent in technical writing skills.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Must be able to communicate with all levels of the organization as well in some cases with customer (during visit).</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Positions require the ability to process information from multiple sources and make decisions based upon sound engineering judgment.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Must be competent in interpreting engineering drawings and Geometric Dimensions & Tolerances.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Experience in implementing improvements in manufacturing, and product quality in the automotive industry preferably.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Experience in ISO 9001:20008 and TS 16949 quality systems, auditing, supplier selection, and production support. (Plus)</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Core tools management experience (SPC, AMEF, PPAP/APQP, Control Plans).</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\"> </div>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\"><strong>REQUISITES</strong></div>\\n\\n<ul style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Education: B.S. Degree in Engineering, Industrial, Mechanic, Electromechanic or similar.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">Certifications or memberships to organizations</div>\\n\\n<ul style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">ASQC Certified Quality Engineer (desired)<br />\\n	Certified Lean Six Sigma Green Belt (desired)</li>\\n</ul>\\n''', 'Active', 1, '2013-03-05', '2013-03-10 18:40:06'),
(8, 1958017, 'Engineering Manager', 'Internal Postings', 'Tijuana', 'B.C.', '$100K+', '''<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">Our client, a leading medical devices manufacturer has an excellent opportunity available for a seasoned Engineering Manager. </div>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">The Sr. Engineering Manager will report directly to the Director of Operations, and will manage the Manufacturing Engineering team.  This individual will develop departmental strategies to implement continuous improvements, determine optimum equipment based on performance and cost, and prioritize engineering staff’s projects.  Also manage and track capital projects, ensuring the proper goals and milestones are met on time and within budget.  Manages capital projects within the manufacturing areas, process and equipment validation activities and ensure overall projects are implemented within budget and within the committed timeline. </div>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\"><strong>ESSENTIAL DUTIES AND RESPONSIBILITIES </strong></div>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\"><strong>Include the following.  Other duties may be assigned. </strong></div>\\n\\n<ul style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Manage Manufacturing Engineering team and operating systems.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Develop and maintain departmental budget.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Lead engineering team to identify projects for process optimization, quality improvements and cost reduction.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Provide technical leadership to support: capital projects, new products, packaging, material testing, and process/product ramp-ups.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Develop strategies for the implementation of measures to improve production methods, equipment performance, and quality of product</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Participate in Design Control gate reviews with the product development teams</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Review test protocols, oversee the execution, and final report approvals.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Required business travel:  15-25%</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\"><strong>REQUIREMENTS | EXPERIENCE NEEDED</strong></div>\\n\\n<ul style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Laser Welding, Cutting, and Engraving</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Resistant Spot Welding</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Physical Vapor Deposition</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">EMI Ceramic Manufacturing – Multi layer Ceramic Capacitors (MLCC)</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">High Vacuum Brazing</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Automated Electrical Testing</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Leak Testing</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">SEM/EDS Material Analysis</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Bachelors Degree in Engineering, 5-10 years of management experience in the medical devices and/or manufacturing industry; or equivalent combination of education and experience.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\"> <strong>What&#39;s In It For You:</strong></div>\\n\\n<ul style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Amazing growth company</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Great salary packages</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Excellent benefits</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Room for professional growth</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Friendly team</li>\\n</ul>\\n''', 'Active', 1, '2013-03-04', '2013-03-10 18:40:06'),
(9, 1958003, 'Human Resources Manager', 'Internal Postings', 'Tillsonburg', 'Ontario', '$90K + 10% Bonus', '''<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">We have an immediate vacancy for a Human Resources Manager. Our client is one of North America’s largest automotive Tier 1 manufacturers and is in need of a strong HR Professional for their facility in Tillsonburg, Ontario.</div>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\"> <strong>RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></div>\\n\\n<ul style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Provide advice and consultancy to ensure compliance with applicable employment legislation</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Develop, leverage and report HR metrics to ensure quality, timely and consistent service delivery</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Promote a culture which values employees and fosters ethical HR practices</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Develop and implement value added, progressive pro-active policies and procedures, strategies, programs (including recruitment and selection, compensation and benefits, health and safety, performance management, training and development, employee relations initiatives) in compliance with regulatory agencies</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Manage recruitment activities, including recruitment plan development, sourcing candidates and retention strategies</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Develop and manage the compensation program, hourly and salary payroll administration, pay equity maintenance and group benefit and pension plan management</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Manage health and safety program and serve as the Management Representative for Joint Health and Safety Committee</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Manage the Employee Performance Management System</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Manage cost effective employee training, development and onboarding initiatives</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Manage employee relations initiatives and cultural and change management initiatives</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Human Resources Information System maintenance and records management</li>\\n</ul>\\n\\n<div style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\"><strong>MINIMUM QUALIFICATIONS:</strong></div>\\n\\n<ul style=\\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 10px;\\">\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Degree in Human Resources Management or related discipline.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">5+ years experience as a Human Resources Manager in the automotive industry (preferably)</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">5+ years labour relations experience (handling grievances, etc.)</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Highly advanced professional writing and oral communication skills.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Ability to interact effectively with employees and management at all levels of the company.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Demonstrated negotiation and facilitation skills.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Excellent judgment, diplomacy, discretion and problem solving skills.</li>\\n	<li style=\\"padding: 0; margin: 0;\\">Intermediate to advanced MS Office skills (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook)</li>\\n</ul>\\n''', 'Active', 1, '2013-03-04', '2013-03-10 18:40:07');

